description:
Paved rail trail in Olympia that intersects with Yelm-Tenino Trail. Total trail 
length is almost 34km.
http://
www.co.thurston.wa.us
/parks/
trails-chehalis-western.htm
directions:
Woodard Bay trail head (north) from I-5:
1. Head southwest on I-5 S toward Exit 109 
2. Take exit 109 for Martin Way toward College St/Sleater-Kinney Rd N for 
350 m
3. Turn right at Martin Way E for 1.0 km
4. Turn right at Sleater Kinney Rd NE for 7.2 km
5. Continue onto 56th Ave NE for 700 m
6. Turn right at Shincke Rd NE for 1.0 km
7. Slight left at Woodard Bay Rd NE for 500 m
8. Slight right on Woodard Bay Rd NE for 200 m
9. Turn right into parking lot
67th Ave tail head (central) from I-5:
1. Head southwest on I-5 S toward Exit 109 
2. Take exit 109 for Martin Way toward College St/Sleater-Kinney Rd N for 
350 m
3. Turn right at Martin Way E for 220 m
4. Take the 1st left onto College St SE for 4.6 km
5. At the traffic circle, continue straight to stay on College St SE for 1.2 km
6. Continue onto Rainier Rd SE for 1.0 km
7. Turn right at 67th Ave SE for 400 m
8. Parking lot straight ahead
title: Chehalis Western Rail Trail
